    "description": "If you're a passionate Risk Analyst with drive and ambition, National Insurance in Pune is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout National Insurance:\nNational Insurance is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n• Proficiency in Credit Analysis\n• Proficiency in Bloomberg Terminal\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in Power BI\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Pune, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with National Insurance!",
